{{Quote|Someone triggered the beast's shock collar.|Grakkus the Hutt|<ref name="Star Wars 12" />}}
A '''shock collar''' was a device placed around the neck of a captive individual or creature in order to shock them into submission.

==History==
When [[Mandalorian]] [[Prime Minister]] [[Almec]]'s [[Mandalorian black market conspiracy|black market operation]] was to be exposed, Almec had Mandalore's ruler, [[Duchess]] [[Satine Kryze]], was fitted with a shock collar. Hoping to have her sign a confession of [[treason]], he [[torture]]d her with it, but as she refused, he threatened to have her nephew, [[Korkie Kryze]], tortured with a shock collar instead. [[Ahsoka Tano]], however, placed the device on him, forcing him to surrender.<ref name="The Academy" />

Practicers of [[slavery]], [[Zygerrian]]s made use of shock collars for their servants. The captive [[Jedi]] Ahsoka Tano and [[Obi-Wan Kenobi]], [[Clone Captain]] [[Rex]], as well as kidnapped [[Togruta]] colonists from [[Kiros]], all were made to wear shock collars until their release by [[Galactic Republic|Republic]] allies.<ref name="Slaves of the Republic" /><ref name="Escape from Kadavo" />

[[Kongo]] the Disemboweler was fitted with a shock collar while fighting in the arena inside the [[palace of Grakkus the Hutt]]. This shock collar was activated by [[Galactic Empire|Imperial]] [[Sergeant]] [[Kreel]], who was undercover as the arena's gamemaster, when Kongo fought [[Luke Skywalker]].<ref name="Star Wars 12" />

